2 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Big game and wildlife highway crossings and accommodations
3 account -- purpose -- funds invested. (1) There is a big game and wildlife highway crossings and
4 accommodations state special revenue account in the state special revenue fund established in 17-2-102
5 administered by the department of fish, wildlife, and parks.
6 (2) The purpose of the account is to provide money exclusively for the design, construction,
7 identification, maintenance, and conservation of wildlife crossings and other related crossing accommodations
8 to improve wildlife permeability in the state, which may include but is not limited to:
9 (a) matching any federal money for a project to design, construct, identify, maintain, or protect
10 wildlife crossings and other related crossing accommodation features;
11 (b) conducting studies on wildlife crossings and other related crossing accommodations;
12 (c) designing or constructing wildlife crossings and other related crossing accommodation
13 features;
14 (d) planning related to wildlife crossings and other related crossing accommodation features,
15 including assessing risk of wildlife disease transmission;
16 (e) staffing needs related to the design, construction, identification, maintenance, and conservation
17 of wildlife crossings and other related crossing accommodation features; and
18 (f) any other needs the department identified in consultation with the department of transportation
19 related to wildlife highway crossing accommodations.
20 (3) There must be deposited into the account transfers, gifts, grants, donations, income from
21 investment of the fund, and any other money distributed or otherwise allocated to the fund.
22 (4) Money in the account may be used to fund the department of transportation for eligible projects
23 or programs as determined by the department of fish, wildlife, and parks. The department of fish, wildlife, and
24 parks shall consult with the department of transportation before funding qualifying projects in the state in
25 accordance with subsection (2).
26 (5) Money that was not encumbered or expended from the account during the previous biennium
27 must remain in the account.
